 <2372070191e24ba4a49378c4a69bd8f0@srbc.net>
Message-ID: <bd913192-dcfa-3c1c-2ea8-7941465fb366@gmail.com>

Dear Matthew,

here is one, maybe not the fastest/shortest, solution:
percentiles <- apply(X = df_ref, MARGIN = 2, FUN = quantile, probs = 
seq(from = 0, to = 1, length.out = 101)[-1])
df_sample$percentile_rank <- vapply(X = colnames(df_sample)[-1], 
FUN.VALUE = numeric(nrow(df_sample)), FUN = function(variable_name) 
findInterval(x = df_sample[, variable_name, drop = TRUE], vec = 
percentiles[, variable_name, drop = TRUE]))

HTH,
?kos Bede-Fazekas
Hungarian Academy of Sciences

